<h4>
        rsync alt.<!-- #$loop:item['xar_title']# -->
               </h4>
<!-- show changelog -->
<!-- end changelog -->
           <span class="xar-sub">
Posted by:                     Anonymous Coward
 on                 November 02, 2005 07:41 AM</span>
       </div>
       <div class="xar-accent xar-cm-comment">

                 
            
              Actually, it's based on rsync, but unison is a great program if you work in more than one location. One problem that can arise with rsync is which direction do you push your data? If changes can be made on either server, than unison manages to smartly decide how to proceed, with prompting the user if necessary. It is both a command line and has a front end, so you can e.g. place it in a cron script to sync. your servers every two hours. It also keeps profiles, so it's easy to set up different directories to sync (or you can specify it all on the CLI). 

                <p>
                    <a href="http://www.linux.com/archive/?module=comments&amp;func=display&amp;cid=1149227" title="Permalink" rel="bookmark">
                       #
                   </a>
               </p>

       </div>

</div>

