       <div class="xar-accent xar-cm-comment">

                 
            
              <i>Splitvt is a tool I can't live without - especially in conjunction w/ screen. It's great for monitoring logfiles (as is multitail).</i><br><br>Why don&#180;t use just GNU Screen for that? Open Screen, create a new &quot;virtual terminal&quot; (or whatever it is called in there), switch to the first terminal and press &quot;Ctrl-a + S&quot; (without quotes). Screen will split the console in two and you can go back and forth using &quot;Ctrl-a + TAB&quot;. When on the &quot;second window&quot;, just use &quot;Ctrl-a + a&quot; or whatever you prefers to use to get on the newly created terminal.<br><br>You can get back to the fullscreen viewing pressing &quot;Ctrl-a + Q&quot;. This way, you can keep using tail normally when monitoring your logs...&lt;nobr&gt; &lt;wbr&gt;&lt;/nobr&gt;:-)<br><br>GNU Screen is incredibly powerful. I&#180;d recommend to anyone interested to give a brief look at its options to leverage all the functionality of this nifty tool. 

                <p>
                    <a href="http://www.linux.com/archive/?module=comments&amp;func=display&amp;cid=1149249" title="Permalink" rel="bookmark">
                       #
                   </a>
               </p>

