<h4>
        Directory bookmarks<!-- #$loop:item['xar_title']# -->
               </h4>
<!-- show changelog -->
<!-- end changelog -->
           <span class="xar-sub">
Posted by:                     Anonymous Coward
 on                 November 02, 2005 01:14 PM</span>
       </div>
       <div class="xar-accent xar-cm-comment">

                 
            
              I wrote a similar shell package that I call dir radar. I optimized on typing, calling the cd command<br><br><br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &quot;d&quot;<br><br>By itself it jumps to the current &quot;Marked&quot; directory, which is marked with<br><br><br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &quot;md&quot;<br><br>Both &quot;d&quot; and &quot;md&quot; can take an arg, which is a tag . In the case of &quot;md&quot;, it mark's the current dir with that tag. In the case of &quot;d&quot; it jumps to it.<br><br>A list of the &quot;bookmarked&quot; dir's can be seen with &quot;dl&quot;. this package is really simple and very fast.<br><br>See &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.orbit2orbit.com/gmd&quot; title=&quot;orbit2orbit.com&quot;&gt;http://www.orbit2orbit.com/gmd&lt;/a orbit2orbit.com&gt;<br> 

                <p>
                    <a href="http://www.linux.com/archive/?module=comments&amp;func=display&amp;cid=1149234" title="Permalink" rel="bookmark">
                       #
                   </a>
               </p>

