<h4>
        These are all tools...<!-- #$loop:item['xar_title']# -->
               </h4>
<!-- show changelog -->
<!-- end changelog -->
           <span class="xar-sub">
Posted by:                     Administrator
 on                 November 02, 2005 07:38 AM</span>
       </div>
       <div class="xar-accent xar-cm-comment">

                 
            
              telnet? Sheeesh. I would point OpenSSH as one of first things *essential* to administering Linux box. My set of tools (in no particular order): OpenLDAP (Directory Service), EVMS (Storage Management), SELinux (MAC Based Security Scheme), Snort (Networked Intrusion Detecition System), Samba (Bridging Linux to Windows Networking World) etc. - these are *services* not just tools. As for tools I would mention My Favourite Scripting Language (that would be Ruby, Python, Java, PERL (order matters) for most).<br />
<br />
I don't know what MP3 encoder has got to do with administration od an Operating System? Also an $EDITOR? Geesh - use gedit if it suits you, it is not essential to administration tasks. Editor is the matter of choice/preferences of user. 

                <p>
                    <a href="http://www.linux.com/archive/?module=comments&amp;func=display&amp;cid=1149264" title="Permalink" rel="bookmark">
                       #
                   </a>
               </p>

       </div>

</div>

